==English==

===Etymology===
From the German name for [[Wikipedia:Saverne|Saverne]], a town in Alsace. Originated from an [[Wikipedia:Saverne Affair|incident]] in 1913 involving an overzealous soldier who wounded a [[cobbler]] for laughing at him, ultimately triggering an intervention from the army who took over the power from local authorities.

